Privacy Policy for "Half a Minute"
Introduction
Welcome to "Half a Minute," developed by Lerikon. Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and share your information when you use our app. This policy is linked on our appâ€™s store listing page in Play Console and is accessible within the app itself.
Data Collection and Use
Types of Data Collected
We do not collect any personal or sensitive user data. The only data we collect pertains to crash logs, which helps us improve the app.
Crash Logs:
Crash Data:
Automatically collected in the event of an app crash to diagnose and fix issues.
Use of Data
App Improvement:
To identify and resolve issues that cause app crashes.
Data Sharing
We do not share any user data with third parties. Crash logs are used internally to enhance app performance and stability.
Data Handling and Security
We implement secure data handling procedures to protect the crash logs from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. This includes:
Encryption:
All crash log data is encrypted during transmission and storage.
Access Controls:
Only authorized personnel have access to the crash log data.
Data Retention and Deletion
Retention:
We retain crash log data for as long as necessary to improve the app's performance and resolve issues.
Deletion:
Crash log data is periodically reviewed and deleted when no longer needed.
Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:
Privacy Point of Contact:
Email: contact@lerikon.nl
Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on our app and on our website. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.
This Privacy Policy is readable in a standard browser without any plug-ins or special handlers and is available on an active, publicly accessible, and non-geofenced URL. The document is non-editable to ensure its integrity and authenticity.
Thank you for using "Half a Minute."
Lerikon